Ronnie Brown <ronnie.profbrown@btinternet.com> writes:

> In view of the recent correspondence which shows that TAC is not
> properly listed by ISI
[...]
> Email from Rodney Chonka to Bob Rosebrugh 02/07/2010
>
> I am pleased to inform you that this journal has been accepted for the
> following Thomson Reuters products beginning with volume 20(2008):
>
> Science Citation Index-Expanded (SCIE)

Just to clarify the situation: the word "expanded" is the key here.  The
main ISI index is just called the Science Citation Index, and as far as
I can tell, it is the one that matters for the various citation statistics
that some administrators unfortunately think are important.  Thomson is
very reluctant to add journals to this index.

